org.eclipse.gef4.mvc.behaviors

Class ContentBehavior<VR>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.gef4.mvc.behaviors.AbstractBehavior<VR>
      • org.eclipse.gef4.mvc.behaviors.ContentBehavior<VR>
  • Type Parameters:
    VR - The visual root node of the UI toolkit used, e.g. javafx.scene.Node in case of JavaFX.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IActivatable, IAdaptable.Bound<IVisualPart<VR,? extends VR>>, IDisposable, IBehavior<VR>

    public class ContentBehavior<VR>
extends AbstractBehavior<VR>
implements IDisposable
    A behavior that can be adapted to an IRootPart or an IContentPart to synchronize the list of IContentPart children and (only in case of an IContentPart) anchorages with the list of content children and anchored.

      • findOrCreatePartFor

        protected IContentPart<VR,? extends VR> findOrCreatePartFor(java.lang.Object content)
        Finds/Revives/Creates an IContentPart for the given content Object. If an IContentPart for the given content Object can be found in the viewer's content-part-map, then this part is returned. If an IContentPart for the given content Object is stored in the injected ContentPartPool, then this part is returned. Otherwise, the injected IContentPartFactory is used to create a new IContentPart for the given content Object.
        Parameters:
        content - The content Object for which the corresponding IContentPart is to be returned.
        Returns:
        The IContentPart corresponding to the given content Object.
